The Center For Stem Cell Science, Hyderabad is an Indian, stem cell research center, located in Hyderabad, India. The center uses adult stem cells to conduct translational research for ailments relating to liver, pancreas, heart, kidney, bone and cartilage disorders.
The institute was formerly known as Centre for Liver Research and Diagnostics. The Institute started its operations in the Deccan College of Medical Sciences. The institute has been recognized for Doctor of Philosophy programme by the Osmania University and Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University.
